modules.description: Provides functions to normalize strings by removing case distinctions, accent marks, or both, using ISO 8859-15 encoding rules. Operates on ASCII-compatible strings with special handling for Latin-1 characters. Used for text normalization in search operations, data deduplication, and locale-aware comparisons.

Provides efficient approximate string matching using edit distance calculations. Operates on strings and lists of strings, supporting fuzzy matching with customizable tolerance levels. Used to find near-matches in user input, spell correction, and data deduplication tasks.

Normalizes strings by stripping case and accents according to ISO 8859-15 rules, supporting ASCII and Latin-1 characters. It handles text normalization for search, deduplication, and locale-sensitive comparisons. Key operations include case folding and accent removal, applied to strings via dedicated functions. Examples include normalizing "Él" to "el" or "HELLO" to "hello".
